beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Pours golden copper with a rapidly diminishing head. Lemongrass and citrusy aroma. Light sweetness, with a lemon/honey finish. Has a creamy texture, light body, with a very abrupt finish. This beer is a very sessionable beer (preferably in summer) , with a refreshing taste and low ABV. I prefer this brew to the Summer Shandy seasonal offering from Leinenkugels.

Pours copper in color with a quickly disappearing head. Aromas of citrus and lemongrass. Malty, sweet taste up front with no bitterness.. Medium palate, with a soft carbonation and quick finish.  Seems to be quite a sessionable lager for those who shy away from hoppy brews.

Bottle. Bready,  mild chocolate aroma. Midnight black in appearance, with a nice pillowy head and nice lacing. Interesting balance between the hops and malts, with sweetness at first with a bitter finish. Thick, creamy texture with soft carbonation. Overall, much better than draught and a step up from stout. Hop-Heads should try this offering from Guinness.

Pours dark brown to almost black with nice fluffy head and medium lacing. Aromas of cocoa and chocolate. Medium bitterness. Full body, creamy, with the malts taking over the palate at the finish. Very sessionable for a porter.
